Opposition leaders blame Syrian and Lebanese governments for Hariri's assassination, demanding Syrian troop withdrawal from Lebanon.
They call on the international community to intervene, citing Hariri's ties to Saudi Arabia.
Saudi Arabia rejects an international investigation, asserting Lebanon's independence.
Hariri, a symbol of Lebanon, was mourned by hundreds of thousands.
Syria denies involvement, but accusations persist.
Hariri's death sparks calls for a change in Lebanon-Syria relations.
Hariri's burial in Beirut unites mourners in grief and anger.
The investigation into his assassination continues, with Syria under scrutiny.
Hariri's legacy as a politician and benefactor lives on
